cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.PL 

The paper proposes a photonic accelerator design for convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which falls under the category of hardware design for AI applications. The Winograd filtering algorithm is used as the basis for the accelerator design, which is commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), which focuses on new hardware and software technologies for computing. The paper also discusses the use of CNNs in computer vision and speech recognition, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AR (Augmented Reality and Virtual Reality) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for improved energy efficiency, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
